@database y " "
@node main
Below are specified FileShield filetypes.
To clear files from FS headers you can also use xfd external
slave from this package. It knows FileShield`s filetypes and some
other made by me.
                        Zeeball

--------------------------------------
   FileShield v1.0/1.1 files:
      
	section	Code,Code
	pea	Program
	rts
	rts
	rts
	section	Program,Code
Program:
	(...)

   No HUNK_END at the end of the added
   reloc.
   filesize: +44
--------------------------------------

   FileShield header added via AsmOne:
   Gives the same as above + HUNK_END
   
   filesize: +48
--------------------------------------
   FileShield v1.2 or newer files:

	section	Code,Code
	pea	Program
	rts
	rts
	ds.w	1
	section	Program,Code
Program:
	(...)

   Contains Reloc32Short
   (without HUNK_END), so needs OS2.0+
   
   filesize: +36
--------------------------------------
@endnode
